# Rust Patterns

## Error Handling
```rust
// BAD: panics in library code
let val = map.get(&key).unwrap();

// GOOD: propagate errors
let val = map.get(&key).ok_or(MyError::KeyNotFound { key })?;
```

## Avoid Unnecessary Cloning
```rust
// BAD: clone when borrow suffices
fn process(data: &Config) {
    let name = data.name.clone();
    log::info!("{name}");
}

// GOOD: borrow
fn process(data: &Config) {
    log::info!("{}", data.name);
}
```

## Feature Gates
- Optional functionality behind Cargo features
- Test-only exports: `#[cfg(any(test, feature = "e2e"))]`
- Hardware tests: `#[ignore]` with descriptive reason

## Lint Expectations
- Prefer `#[expect(lint, reason = "...")]` over `#[allow(lint)]`
- Never suppress lints at file level without `reason` parameter
- `dead_code` on struct fields reserved for future use: `#[allow(dead_code, reason = "...")]`

## Unsafe Code
- Only in `coral-driver` (hardware ioctl, MMIO, DMA)
- Every `unsafe` block has `// SAFETY: ...` comment
- Wrap unsafe in safe abstractions at module boundary
